{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#2142: Suspense regression when toggling an async component in rc.12",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:28:15.826885+00:00",
  "text": "Suspense regression when toggling an async component in rc.12\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.0-rc.12\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://jsfiddle.net/v0onkyej/](https://jsfiddle.net/v0onkyej/)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nThis is based on a comment I added on #3132 but I'm afraid it went unnoticed.\r\nJust to make sure we are not missing anything.\r\n\r\nConsider:\r\n```html\r\n<button @click=\"toggled = !toggled\">Toggle {{ toggled }}</button>\r\n<Suspense>\r\n  <div v-if=\"toggled\">\r\n    <hello />\r\n  </div>\r\n  <template #fallback>Loading...</template>\r\n</Suspense>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nIn rc.10, the Loading indicator is displayed.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nIn rc.12, the Loading indicator is not displayed.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: suspense"
  ],
